This paper deals with network MIMO techniques in an indoor wireless environment, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of non-ideal hardware, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of interference alignment and coordinated multi-point techniques also involves system-level optimization and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the techniques using a real-world wireless testbed, which could fall under the category of computer architecture and robotics (cs.AR).
